      "title": "H∞ design with pole placement constraints: an LMI approach",
      "abstract": "1,031,683. Fluid pressure servomotor control system. E. MURAKAMI. Feb. 1,1963 [Feb. 3, 1962], No. 4324/63. Heading G3P. A fluid flow control valve comprises a main valve member actuated in response to the inlet or outlet pressure. A main valve closure 3, cooperates with a seat 2 and the inlet pressure is fed through a passage 1A and a part 7a to the top of a piston 9. The inlet pressure is also supplied through a pipe 27a to act continuously on a small diameter piston 19a connected to one end of a rack 20 of which the other end is connected to a larger diameter piston 19. Movement of the rack rotates a pinion 22 which rotates a valve member 11 to lift the valve or lever the valve into its seating 10a formed on the piston 9. The valve 11 controls leakage of inlet pressure from above the piston to the outlet to control the opening of the main valve 2, 3. Fluid pressure supplied and exhausted from the space 14 housing the larger piston 19 is controlled in response to inlet and outlet pressure. When the valve 3 acts as a pressure relief valve, the inlet pressure in passage 7 is fed through a passage 27, fig. 2 (not shown) to a Bourdon tube 34. A rise in the inlet pressure above a predetermined valve,determined by the position of a rod 38 causes a lever 36, pivoted to the rod 38, to rotate and act through a rod 40 to close a valve 29a and open a valve 30a whereby inlet pressure in the passage 27 is fed past the open valve 30a to a passage 28 which leads to the chamber 14 and thus causes the rack to move to the right and hence valve 3 to open. When the inlet pressure again falls, the valve 30a closes and the valve 29a opens connecting passage 28 to a passage 32 which leads to the main valve outlet and the rack moves to the left under the action of inlet pressure on the smaller piston 19a thus closing the valve. When the main valve 3 is controlled in response to outlet pressure, the outlet pressure is fed to the Bourdon tube and the valves 29a, 30a are so arranged that a rise in outlet pressure closes the main valve and a fall in outlet pressure opens this valve. In a further modification the movement of the rack rotates the pinion which directly rotates a two or three-way plug valve."
